V8 is Googleâ€™s open source high-performance JavaScript and WebAssembly engine, written in C++. It is used in Chrome and in Node.js, among others. It implements ECMAScript and WebAssembly, and runs on Windows, macOS, and Linux systems that use x64, IA-32, or ARM processors. V8 can be embedded into any C++ application.

5// A Disassembler object is used to disassemble a block of code instruction by
6// instruction. The default implementation of the NameConverter object can be
7// overriden to modify register names or to do symbol lookup on addresses.
8//
9// The example below will disassemble a block of code and print it to stdout.
10//
11// NameConverter converter;
12// Disassembler d(converter);
13// for (uint8_t* pc = begin; pc < end;) {
14// v8::base::EmbeddedVector<char, 256> buffer;
15// uint8_t* prev_pc = pc;
16// pc += d.InstructionDecode(buffer, pc);
17// printf("%p %08x %s\n",
18// prev_pc, *reinterpret_cast<int32_t*>(prev_pc), buffer);
19// }
20//
21// The Disassembler class also has a convenience method to disassemble a block
22// of code into a FILE*, meaning that the above functionality could also be
23// achieved by just calling Disassembler::Disassemble(stdout, begin, end);
24

26#include <stdarg.h>
27#include <stdio.h>
28#include <string.h>

42// Decoder decodes and disassembles instructions into an output buffer.
43// It uses the converter to convert register names and call destinations into
44// more informative description.
45class Decoder {
46 public:
47 Decoder(const disasm::NameConverter& converter,
48 v8::base::Vector<char> out_buffer)
49 : converter_(converter), out_buffer_(out_buffer), out_buffer_pos_(0) {
50 out_buffer_[out_buffer_pos_] = '\0';
51 }
52
53 ~Decoder() {}
54 Decoder(const Decoder&) = delete;
55 Decoder& operator=(const Decoder&) = delete;
56
57 // Writes one disassembled instruction into 'buffer' (0-terminated).
58 // Returns the length of the disassembled machine instruction in bytes.
59 int InstructionDecode(uint8_t* instruction);
60
61 private:

63 void PrintChar(const char ch);

164// Support for assertions in the Decoder formatting functions.
165#define STRING_STARTS_WITH(string, compare_string) \
166 (strncmp(string, compare_string, strlen(compare_string)) == 0)

168// Append the ch to the output buffer.
169void Decoder::PrintChar(const char ch) { out_buffer_[out_buffer_pos_++] = ch; }
170
171// Append the str to the output buffer.
172void Decoder::Print(const char* str) {
173 char cur = *str++;
174 while (cur != '\0' && (out_buffer_pos_ < (out_buffer_.length() - 1))) {
175 PrintChar(cur);
176 cur = *str++;
177 }
178 out_buffer_[out_buffer_pos_] = 0;
179}

260void Decoder::PrintTarget(Instruction* instr) {
261 if (Assembler::IsJalr(instr->InstructionBits())) {
262 if (Assembler::IsAuipc((instr - 4)->InstructionBits()) &&
263 (instr - 4)->RdValue() == instr->Rs1Value()) {
264 int32_t imm = Assembler::BrachlongOffset((instr - 4)->InstructionBits(),
265 instr->InstructionBits());
266 const char* target =
267 converter_.NameOfAddress(reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(instr - 4) + imm);
268 out_buffer_pos_ +=
269 base::SNPrintF(out_buffer_ + out_buffer_pos_, " -> %s", target);
270 return;
271 }
272 }
273}

403void Decoder::PrintAcquireRelease(Instruction* instr) {
404 bool aq = instr->AqValue();
405 bool rl = instr->RlValue();
406 if (aq || rl) {
407 out_buffer_pos_ += base::SNPrintF(out_buffer_ + out_buffer_pos_, ".");
408 }
409 if (aq) {
410 out_buffer_pos_ += base::SNPrintF(out_buffer_ + out_buffer_pos_, "aq");
411 }
412 if (rl) {
413 out_buffer_pos_ += base::SNPrintF(out_buffer_ + out_buffer_pos_, "rl");
414 }
415}

417void Decoder::PrintCSRReg(Instruction* instr) {
418 int32_t csr_reg = instr->CsrValue();
419 std::string s;
420 switch (csr_reg) {
421 case csr_fflags: // Floating-Point Accrued Exceptions (RW)
422 s = "csr_fflags";
423 break;
424 case csr_frm: // Floating-Point Dynamic Rounding Mode (RW)
425 s = "csr_frm";
426 break;
427 case csr_fcsr: // Floating-Point Control and Status Register (RW)
428 s = "csr_fcsr";
429 break;
430 case csr_cycle:
431 s = "csr_cycle";
432 break;
433 case csr_time:
434 s = "csr_time";
435 break;
436 case csr_instret:
437 s = "csr_instret";
438 break;
439 case csr_cycleh:
440 s = "csr_cycleh";
441 break;
442 case csr_timeh:
443 s = "csr_timeh";
444 break;
445 case csr_instreth:
446 s = "csr_instreth";
447 break;
448 default:
449 UNREACHABLE();
450 }
451 out_buffer_pos_ +=
452 base::SNPrintF(out_buffer_ + out_buffer_pos_, "%s", s.c_str());
453}
454
455void Decoder::PrintRoundingMode(Instruction* instr) {
456 int frm = instr->RoundMode();
457 std::string s;
458 switch (frm) {
459 case RNE:
460 s = "RNE";
461 break;
462 case RTZ:
463 s = "RTZ";
464 break;
465 case RDN:
466 s = "RDN";
467 break;
468 case RUP:
469 s = "RUP";
470 break;
471 case RMM:
472 s = "RMM";
473 break;
474 case DYN:
475 s = "DYN";
476 break;
477 default:
478 UNREACHABLE();
479 }
480 out_buffer_pos_ +=
481 base::SNPrintF(out_buffer_ + out_buffer_pos_, "%s", s.c_str());
482}
483
484void Decoder::PrintMemoryOrder(Instruction* instr, bool is_pred) {
485 int memOrder = instr->MemoryOrder(is_pred);
486 std::string s;
487 if ((memOrder & PSI) == PSI) {
488 s += "i";
489 }
490 if ((memOrder & PSO) == PSO) {
491 s += "o";
492 }
493 if ((memOrder & PSR) == PSR) {
494 s += "r";
495 }
496 if ((memOrder & PSW) == PSW) {
497 s += "w";
498 }
499 out_buffer_pos_ +=
500 base::SNPrintF(out_buffer_ + out_buffer_pos_, "%s", s.c_str());
501}

506// Handle all register based formatting in this function to reduce the
507// complexity of FormatOption.
508int Decoder::FormatRegister(Instruction* instr, const char* format) {
509 DCHECK_EQ(format[0], 'r');
510 if (format[1] == 's') { // 'rs[12]: Rs register.
511 if (format[2] == '1') {
512 int reg = instr->Rs1Value();
513 PrintRegister(reg);
514 return 3;
515 } else if (format[2] == '2') {
516 int reg = instr->Rs2Value();
517 PrintRegister(reg);
518 return 3;
519 }
520 UNREACHABLE();
521 } else if (format[1] == 'd') { // 'rd: rd register.
522 int reg = instr->RdValue();
523 PrintRegister(reg);
524 return 2;
525 }
526 UNREACHABLE();
527}
528
529// Handle all FPUregister based formatting in this function to reduce the
530// complexity of FormatOption.
531int Decoder::FormatFPURegisterOrRoundMode(Instruction* instr,
532 const char* format) {
533 DCHECK_EQ(format[0], 'f');
534 if (format[1] == 's') { // 'fs[1-3]: Rs register.
535 if (format[2] == '1') {
536 int reg = instr->Rs1Value();
537 PrintFPURegister(reg);
538 return 3;
539 } else if (format[2] == '2') {
540 int reg = instr->Rs2Value();
541 PrintFPURegister(reg);
542 return 3;
543 } else if (format[2] == '3') {
544 int reg = instr->Rs3Value();
545 PrintFPURegister(reg);
546 return 3;
547 }
548 UNREACHABLE();
549 } else if (format[1] == 'd') { // 'fd: fd register.
550 int reg = instr->RdValue();
551 PrintFPURegister(reg);
552 return 2;
553 } else if (format[1] == 'r') { // 'frm
554 DCHECK(STRING_STARTS_WITH(format, "frm"));
555 PrintRoundingMode(instr);
556 return 3;
557 }
558 UNREACHABLE();
559}
560
561// Handle all C extension register based formatting in this function to reduce
562// the complexity of FormatOption.
563int Decoder::FormatRvcRegister(Instruction* instr, const char* format) {
564 DCHECK_EQ(format[0], 'C');
565 DCHECK(format[1] == 'r' || format[1] == 'f');
566 if (format[2] == 's') { // 'Crs[12]: Rs register.
567 if (format[3] == '1') {
568 if (format[4] == 's') { // 'Crs1s: 3-bits register
569 int reg = instr->RvcRs1sValue();
570 if (format[1] == 'r') {
571 PrintRegister(reg);
572 } else if (format[1] == 'f') {
573 PrintFPURegister(reg);
574 }
575 return 5;
576 }
577 int reg = instr->RvcRs1Value();
578 if (format[1] == 'r') {
579 PrintRegister(reg);
580 } else if (format[1] == 'f') {
581 PrintFPURegister(reg);
582 }
583 return 4;
584 } else if (format[3] == '2') {
585 if (format[4] == 's') { // 'Crs2s: 3-bits register
586 int reg = instr->RvcRs2sValue();
587 if (format[1] == 'r') {
588 PrintRegister(reg);
589 } else if (format[1] == 'f') {
590 PrintFPURegister(reg);
591 }
592 return 5;
593 }
594 int reg = instr->RvcRs2Value();
595 if (format[1] == 'r') {
596 PrintRegister(reg);
597 } else if (format[1] == 'f') {
598 PrintFPURegister(reg);
599 }
600 return 4;
601 }
602 UNREACHABLE();
603 } else if (format[2] == 'd') { // 'Crd: rd register.
604 int reg = instr->RvcRdValue();
605 if (format[1] == 'r') {
606 PrintRegister(reg);
607 } else if (format[1] == 'f') {
608 PrintFPURegister(reg);
609 }
610 return 3;
611 }
612 UNREACHABLE();
613}
614
615// Handle all C extension immediates based formatting in this function to reduce
616// the complexity of FormatOption.
617int Decoder::FormatRvcImm(Instruction* instr, const char* format) {
618 // TODO(riscv): add other rvc imm format
619 DCHECK(STRING_STARTS_WITH(format, "Cimm"));
620 if (format[4] == '6') {
621 if (format[5] == 'U') {
622 DCHECK(STRING_STARTS_WITH(format, "Cimm6U"));
623 PrintRvcImm6U(instr);
624 return 6;
625 } else if (format[5] == 'A') {
626 if (format[9] == '1' && format[10] == '6') {
627 DCHECK(STRING_STARTS_WITH(format, "Cimm6Addi16sp"));
628 PrintRvcImm6Addi16sp(instr);
629 return 13;
630 }
631 UNREACHABLE();
632 } else if (format[5] == 'L') {
633 if (format[6] == 'd') {
634 if (format[7] == 's') {
635 DCHECK(STRING_STARTS_WITH(format, "Cimm6Ldsp"));
636 PrintRvcImm6Ldsp(instr);
637 return 9;
638 }
639 } else if (format[6] == 'w') {
640 if (format[7] == 's') {
641 DCHECK(STRING_STARTS_WITH(format, "Cimm6Lwsp"));
642 PrintRvcImm6Lwsp(instr);
643 return 9;
644 }
645 }
646 UNREACHABLE();
647 } else if (format[5] == 'S') {
648 if (format[6] == 'w') {
649 DCHECK(STRING_STARTS_WITH(format, "Cimm6Swsp"));
650 PrintRvcImm6Swsp(instr);
651 return 9;
652 } else if (format[6] == 'd') {
653 DCHECK(STRING_STARTS_WITH(format, "Cimm6Sdsp"));
654 PrintRvcImm6Sdsp(instr);
655 return 9;
656 }
657 UNREACHABLE();
658 }
659 PrintRvcImm6(instr);
660 return 5;
661 } else if (format[4] == '5') {
662 DCHECK(STRING_STARTS_WITH(format, "Cimm5"));
663 if (format[5] == 'W') {
664 DCHECK(STRING_STARTS_WITH(format, "Cimm5W"));
665 PrintRvcImm5W(instr);
666 return 6;
667 } else if (format[5] == 'D') {
668 DCHECK(STRING_STARTS_WITH(format, "Cimm5D"));
669 PrintRvcImm5D(instr);
670 return 6;
671 }
672 UNREACHABLE();
673 } else if (format[4] == '8') {
674 DCHECK(STRING_STARTS_WITH(format, "Cimm8"));
675 if (format[5] == 'A') {
676 DCHECK(STRING_STARTS_WITH(format, "Cimm8Addi4spn"));
677 PrintRvcImm8Addi4spn(instr);
678 return 13;
679 } else if (format[5] == 'B') {
680 DCHECK(STRING_STARTS_WITH(format, "Cimm8B"));
681 PrintRvcImm8B(instr);
682 return 6;
683 }
684 UNREACHABLE();
685 } else if (format[4] == '1') {
686 DCHECK(STRING_STARTS_WITH(format, "Cimm1"));
687 if (format[5] == '1') {
688 DCHECK(STRING_STARTS_WITH(format, "Cimm11CJ"));
689 PrintRvcImm11CJ(instr);
690 return 8;
691 }
692 UNREACHABLE();
693 }
694 UNREACHABLE();
695}
696
697// FormatOption takes a formatting string and interprets it based on
698// the current instructions. The format string points to the first
699// character of the option string (the option escape has already been
700// consumed by the caller.) FormatOption returns the number of
701// characters that were consumed from the formatting string.
702int Decoder::FormatOption(Instruction* instr, const char* format) {
703 switch (format[0]) {
704 case 'C': { // `C extension
705 if (format[1] == 'r' || format[1] == 'f') {
706 return FormatRvcRegister(instr, format);
707 } else if (format[1] == 'i') {
708 return FormatRvcImm(instr, format);
709 } else if (format[1] == 's') {
710 DCHECK(STRING_STARTS_WITH(format, "Cshamt"));
711 PrintRvcShamt(instr);
712 return 6;
713 }
714 UNREACHABLE();
715 }
716 case 'c': { // `csr: CSR registers
717 if (format[1] == 's') {
718 if (format[2] == 'r') {
719 PrintCSRReg(instr);
720 return 3;
721 }
722 }
723 UNREACHABLE();
724 }
725 case 'i': { // 'imm12, 'imm12x, 'imm20U, or 'imm20J: Immediates.
726 if (format[3] == '1') {
727 if (format[4] == '2') {
728 DCHECK(STRING_STARTS_WITH(format, "imm12"));
729 if (format[5] == 'x') {
730 PrintImm12X(instr);
731 return 6;
732 }
733 PrintImm12(instr);
734 return 5;
735 }
736 } else if (format[3] == '2' && format[4] == '0') {
737 DCHECK(STRING_STARTS_WITH(format, "imm20"));
738 switch (format[5]) {
739 case 'U':
740 DCHECK(STRING_STARTS_WITH(format, "imm20U"));
741 PrintImm20U(instr);
742 break;
743 case 'J':
744 DCHECK(STRING_STARTS_WITH(format, "imm20J"));
745 PrintImm20J(instr);
746 break;
747 }
748 return 6;
749 }
750 UNREACHABLE();
751 }
752 case 'o': { // 'offB or 'offS: Offsets.
753 if (format[3] == 'B') {
754 DCHECK(STRING_STARTS_WITH(format, "offB"));
755 PrintBranchOffset(instr);
756 return 4;
757 } else if (format[3] == 'S') {
758 DCHECK(STRING_STARTS_WITH(format, "offS"));
759 PrintStoreOffset(instr);
760 return 4;
761 }
762 UNREACHABLE();
763 }
764 case 'r': { // 'r: registers.
765 return FormatRegister(instr, format);
766 }
767 case 'f': { // 'f: FPUregisters or `frm
768 return FormatFPURegisterOrRoundMode(instr, format);
769 }
770 case 'a': { // 'a: Atomic acquire and release.
771 PrintAcquireRelease(instr);
772 return 1;
773 }
774 case 'p': { // `pre
775 DCHECK(STRING_STARTS_WITH(format, "pre"));
776 PrintMemoryOrder(instr, true);
777 return 3;
778 }
779 case 's': { // 's32 or 's64: Shift amount.
780 if (format[1] == '3') {
781 DCHECK(STRING_STARTS_WITH(format, "s32"));
782 PrintShamt32(instr);
783 return 3;
784 } else if (format[1] == '6') {
785 DCHECK(STRING_STARTS_WITH(format, "s64"));
786 PrintShamt(instr);
787 return 3;
788 } else if (format[1] == 'u') {
789 DCHECK(STRING_STARTS_WITH(format, "suc"));
790 PrintMemoryOrder(instr, false);
791 return 3;
792 } else if (format[1] == 'e') {
793 DCHECK(STRING_STARTS_WITH(format, "sew"));
794 PrintRvvSEW(instr);
795 return 3;
796 } else if (format[1] == 'i') {
797 DCHECK(STRING_STARTS_WITH(format, "simm5"));
798 PrintRvvSimm5(instr);
799 return 5;
800 }
801 UNREACHABLE();
802 }
803 case 'v': {
804 if (format[1] == 'd') {
805 DCHECK(STRING_STARTS_WITH(format, "vd"));
806 PrintVd(instr);
807 return 2;
808 } else if (format[2] == '1') {
809 DCHECK(STRING_STARTS_WITH(format, "vs1"));
810 PrintVs1(instr);
811 return 3;
812 } else if (format[2] == '2') {
813 DCHECK(STRING_STARTS_WITH(format, "vs2"));
814 PrintVs2(instr);
815 return 3;
816 } else {
817 DCHECK(STRING_STARTS_WITH(format, "vm"));
818 PrintRvvVm(instr);
819 return 2;
820 }
821 }
822 case 'l': {
823 DCHECK(STRING_STARTS_WITH(format, "lmul"));
824 PrintRvvLMUL(instr);
825 return 4;
826 }
827 case 'u': {
828 if (STRING_STARTS_WITH(format, "uimm5")) {
829 PrintRvvUimm5(instr);
830 return 5;
831 } else {
832 DCHECK(STRING_STARTS_WITH(format, "uimm"));
833 PrintUimm(instr);
834 return 4;
835 }
836 }
837 case 't': { // 'target: target of branch instructions'
838 DCHECK(STRING_STARTS_WITH(format, "target"));
839 PrintTarget(instr);
840 return 6;
841 }
842 }
843 UNREACHABLE();
844}
845
846// Format takes a formatting string for a whole instruction and prints it into
847// the output buffer. All escaped options are handed to FormatOption to be
848// parsed further.
849void Decoder::Format(Instruction* instr, const char* format) {
850 char cur = *format++;
851 while ((cur != 0) && (out_buffer_pos_ < (out_buffer_.length() - 1))) {
852 if (cur == '\'') { // Single quote is used as the formatting escape.
853 format += FormatOption(instr, format);
854 } else {
855 out_buffer_[out_buffer_pos_++] = cur;
856 }
857 cur = *format++;
858 }
859 out_buffer_[out_buffer_pos_] = '\0';
860}
861
862// For currently unimplemented decodings the disassembler calls Unknown(instr)
863// which will just print "unknown" of the instruction bits.
864void Decoder::Unknown(Instruction* instr) { Format(instr, "unknown"); }
865
866// RISCV Instruction Decode Routine
867void Decoder::DecodeRType(Instruction* instr) {
868 switch (instr->InstructionBits() & kRTypeMask) {
869 case RO_ADD:
870 Format(instr, "add 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
871 break;
872 case RO_SUB:
873 if (instr->Rs1Value() == zero_reg.code())
874 Format(instr, "neg 'rd, 'rs2");
875 else
876 Format(instr, "sub 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
877 break;
878 case RO_SLL:
879 Format(instr, "sll 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
880 break;
881 case RO_SLT:
882 if (instr->Rs2Value() == zero_reg.code())
883 Format(instr, "sltz 'rd, 'rs1");
884 else if (instr->Rs1Value() == zero_reg.code())
885 Format(instr, "sgtz 'rd, 'rs2");
886 else
887 Format(instr, "slt 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
888 break;
889 case RO_SLTU:
890 if (instr->Rs1Value() == zero_reg.code())
891 Format(instr, "snez 'rd, 'rs2");
892 else
893 Format(instr, "sltu 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
894 break;
895 case RO_XOR:
896 Format(instr, "xor 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
897 break;
898 case RO_SRL:
899 Format(instr, "srl 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
900 break;
901 case RO_SRA:
902 Format(instr, "sra 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
903 break;
904 case RO_OR:
905 Format(instr, "or 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
906 break;
907 case RO_AND:
908 Format(instr, "and 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
909 break;
910 case RO_ANDN:
911 Format(instr, "andn 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
912 break;
913 case RO_ORN:
914 Format(instr, "orn 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
915 break;
916 case RO_XNOR:
917 Format(instr, "xnor 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
918 break;
919#ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_64_BIT
920 case RO_ADDW:
921 Format(instr, "addw 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
922 break;
923 case RO_ADDUW:
924 if (instr->Rs2Value() == zero_reg.code()) {
925 Format(instr, "zext.w 'rd, 'rs1");
926 } else {
927 Format(instr, "add.uw 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
928 }
929 break;
930 case RO_SUBW:
931 if (instr->Rs1Value() == zero_reg.code())
932 Format(instr, "negw 'rd, 'rs2");
933 else
934 Format(instr, "subw 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
935 break;
936 case RO_SLLW:
937 Format(instr, "sllw 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
938 break;
939 case RO_SRLW:
940 Format(instr, "srlw 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
941 break;
942 case RO_SRAW:
943 Format(instr, "sraw 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
944 break;
945#endif /* V8_TARGET_ARCH_64_BIT */
946 // TODO(riscv): Add RISCV M extension macro
947 case RO_MUL:
948 Format(instr, "mul 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
949 break;
950 case RO_MULH:
951 Format(instr, "mulh 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
952 break;
953 case RO_MULHSU:
954 Format(instr, "mulhsu 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
955 break;
956 case RO_MULHU:
957 Format(instr, "mulhu 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
958 break;
959 case RO_DIV:
960 Format(instr, "div 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
961 break;
962 case RO_DIVU:
963 Format(instr, "divu 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
964 break;
965 case RO_REM:
966 Format(instr, "rem 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
967 break;
968 case RO_REMU:
969 Format(instr, "remu 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
970 break;
971#ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_64_BIT
972 case RO_MULW:
973 Format(instr, "mulw 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
974 break;
975 case RO_DIVW:
976 Format(instr, "divw 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
977 break;
978 case RO_DIVUW:
979 Format(instr, "divuw 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
980 break;
981 case RO_REMW:
982 Format(instr, "remw 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
983 break;
984 case RO_REMUW:
985 Format(instr, "remuw 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
986 break;
987 case RO_SH1ADDUW:
988 Format(instr, "sh1add.uw 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
989 break;
990 case RO_SH2ADDUW:
991 Format(instr, "sh2add.uw 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
992 break;
993 case RO_SH3ADDUW:
994 Format(instr, "sh3add.uw 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
995 break;
996 case RO_ROLW:
997 Format(instr, "rolw 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
998 break;
999 case RO_RORW:
1000 Format(instr, "rorw 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
1001 break;
1002#endif /*V8_TARGET_ARCH_64_BIT*/
1003 case RO_SH1ADD:
1004 Format(instr, "sh1add 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
1005 break;
1006 case RO_SH2ADD:
1007 Format(instr, "sh2add 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
1008 break;
1009 case RO_SH3ADD:
1010 Format(instr, "sh3add 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
1011 break;
1012 case RO_MAX:
1013 Format(instr, "max 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
1014 break;
1015 case RO_MAXU:
1016 Format(instr, "maxu 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
1017 break;
1018 case RO_MIN:
1019 Format(instr, "min 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
1020 break;
1021 case RO_MINU:
1022 Format(instr, "minu 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
1023 break;
1024 case RO_ZEXTH:
1025 Format(instr, "zext.h 'rd, 'rs1");
1026 break;
1027 case RO_ROL:
1028 Format(instr, "rol 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
1029 break;
1030 case RO_ROR:
1031 Format(instr, "ror 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
1032 break;
1033 case RO_BCLR:
1034 Format(instr, "bclr 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
1035 break;
1036 case RO_BEXT:
1037 Format(instr, "bext 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
1038 break;
1039 case RO_BINV:
1040 Format(instr, "binv 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
1041 break;
1042 case RO_BSET:
1043 Format(instr, "bset 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
1044 break;
1045 case RO_CZERO_EQZ:
1046 Format(instr, "czero.eqz 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
1047 break;
1048 case RO_CZERO_NEZ:
1049 Format(instr, "czero.nez 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
1050 break;
1051 // TODO(riscv): End Add RISCV M extension macro
1052 default: {
1053 switch (instr->BaseOpcode()) {
1054 case AMO:
1055 DecodeRAType(instr);
1056 break;
1057 case OP_FP:
1058 DecodeRFPType(instr);
1059 break;
1060 default:
1061 PrintF("instr:%x\n", instr->InstructionBits());
1062 UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
1063 }
1064 }
1065 }
1066}

1068void Decoder::DecodeRAType(Instruction* instr) {
1069 // TODO(riscv): Add macro for RISCV A extension
1070 // Special handling for A extension instructions because it uses func5
1071 // For all A extension instruction, V8 simulator is pure sequential. No
1072 // Memory address lock or other synchronizaiton behaviors.
1073 switch (instr->InstructionBits() & kRATypeMask) {
1074 case RO_LR_W:
1075 Format(instr, "lr.w'a 'rd, ('rs1)");
1076 break;
1077 case RO_SC_W:
1078 Format(instr, "sc.w'a 'rd, 'rs2, ('rs1)");
1079 break;
1080 case RO_AMOSWAP_W:
1081 Format(instr, "amoswap.w'a 'rd, 'rs2, ('rs1)");
1082 break;
1083 case RO_AMOADD_W:
1084 Format(instr, "amoadd.w'a 'rd, 'rs2, ('rs1)");
1085 break;
1086 case RO_AMOXOR_W:
1087 Format(instr, "amoxor.w'a 'rd, 'rs2, ('rs1)");
1088 break;
1089 case RO_AMOAND_W:
1090 Format(instr, "amoand.w'a 'rd, 'rs2, ('rs1)");
1091 break;
1092 case RO_AMOOR_W:
1093 Format(instr, "amoor.w'a 'rd, 'rs2, ('rs1)");
1094 break;
1095 case RO_AMOMIN_W:
1096 Format(instr, "amomin.w'a 'rd, 'rs2, ('rs1)");
1097 break;
1098 case RO_AMOMAX_W:
1099 Format(instr, "amomax.w'a 'rd, 'rs2, ('rs1)");
1100 break;
1101 case RO_AMOMINU_W:
1102 Format(instr, "amominu.w'a 'rd, 'rs2, ('rs1)");
1103 break;
1104 case RO_AMOMAXU_W:
1105 Format(instr, "amomaxu.w'a 'rd, 'rs2, ('rs1)");
1106 break;
1107#ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_64_BIT
1108 case RO_LR_D:
1109 Format(instr, "lr.d'a 'rd, ('rs1)");
1110 break;
1111 case RO_SC_D:
1112 Format(instr, "sc.d'a 'rd, 'rs2, ('rs1)");
1113 break;
1114 case RO_AMOSWAP_D:
1115 Format(instr, "amoswap.d'a 'rd, 'rs2, ('rs1)");
1116 break;
1117 case RO_AMOADD_D:
1118 Format(instr, "amoadd.d'a 'rd, 'rs2, ('rs1)");
1119 break;
1120 case RO_AMOXOR_D:
1121 Format(instr, "amoxor.d'a 'rd, 'rs2, ('rs1)");
1122 break;
1123 case RO_AMOAND_D:
1124 Format(instr, "amoand.d'a 'rd, 'rs2, ('rs1)");
1125 break;
1126 case RO_AMOOR_D:
1127 Format(instr, "amoor.d'a 'rd, 'rs2, ('rs1)");
1128 break;
1129 case RO_AMOMIN_D:
1130 Format(instr, "amomin.d'a 'rd, 'rs2, ('rs1)");
1131 break;
1132 case RO_AMOMAX_D:
1133 Format(instr, "amoswap.d'a 'rd, 'rs2, ('rs1)");
1134 break;
1135 case RO_AMOMINU_D:
1136 Format(instr, "amominu.d'a 'rd, 'rs2, ('rs1)");
1137 break;
1138 case RO_AMOMAXU_D:
1139 Format(instr, "amomaxu.d'a 'rd, 'rs2, ('rs1)");
1140 break;
1141#endif /*V8_TARGET_ARCH_64_BIT*/
1142 // TODO(riscv): End Add macro for RISCV A extension
1143 default: {
1144 UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
1145 }
1146 }
1147}
1148
1149void Decoder::DecodeRFPType(Instruction* instr) {
1150 // OP_FP instructions (F/D) uses func7 first. Some further uses fun3 and rs2()
1151
1152 // kRATypeMask is only for func7
1153 switch (instr->InstructionBits() & kRFPTypeMask) {
1154 // TODO(riscv): Add macro for RISCV F extension
1155 case RO_FADD_S:
1156 Format(instr, "fadd.s 'fd, 'fs1, 'fs2");
1157 break;
1158 case RO_FSUB_S:
1159 Format(instr, "fsub.s 'fd, 'fs1, 'fs2");
1160 break;
1161 case RO_FMUL_S:
1162 Format(instr, "fmul.s 'fd, 'fs1, 'fs2");
1163 break;
1164 case RO_FDIV_S:
1165 Format(instr, "fdiv.s 'fd, 'fs1, 'fs2");
1166 break;
1167 case RO_FSQRT_S:
1168 Format(instr, "fsqrt.s 'fd, 'fs1");
1169 break;
1170 case RO_FSGNJ_S: { // RO_FSGNJN_S RO_FSGNJX_S
1171 switch (instr->Funct3Value()) {
1172 case 0b000: // RO_FSGNJ_S
1173 if (instr->Rs1Value() == instr->Rs2Value())
1174 Format(instr, "fmv.s 'fd, 'fs1");
1175 else
1176 Format(instr, "fsgnj.s 'fd, 'fs1, 'fs2");
1177 break;
1178 case 0b001: // RO_FSGNJN_S
1179 if (instr->Rs1Value() == instr->Rs2Value())
1180 Format(instr, "fneg.s 'fd, 'fs1");
1181 else
1182 Format(instr, "fsgnjn.s 'fd, 'fs1, 'fs2");
1183 break;
1184 case 0b010: // RO_FSGNJX_S
1185 if (instr->Rs1Value() == instr->Rs2Value())
1186 Format(instr, "fabs.s 'fd, 'fs1");
1187 else
1188 Format(instr, "fsgnjx.s 'fd, 'fs1, 'fs2");
1189 break;
1190 default:
1191 UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
1192 }
1193 break;
1194 }
1195 case RO_FMIN_S: { // RO_FMAX_S
1196 switch (instr->Funct3Value()) {
1197 case 0b000: // RO_FMIN_S
1198 Format(instr, "fmin.s 'fd, 'fs1, 'fs2");
1199 break;
1200 case 0b001: // RO_FMAX_S
1201 Format(instr, "fmax.s 'fd, 'fs1, 'fs2");
1202 break;
1203 default:
1204 UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
1205 }
1206 break;
1207 }
1208 case RO_FCVT_W_S: { // RO_FCVT_WU_S , 64F RO_FCVT_L_S RO_FCVT_LU_S
1209 switch (instr->Rs2Value()) {
1210 case 0b00000: // RO_FCVT_W_S
1211 Format(instr, "fcvt.w.s ['frm] 'rd, 'fs1");
1212 break;
1213 case 0b00001: // RO_FCVT_WU_S
1214 Format(instr, "fcvt.wu.s ['frm] 'rd, 'fs1");
1215 break;
1216#ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_64_BIT
1217 case 0b00010: // RO_FCVT_L_S
1218 Format(instr, "fcvt.l.s ['frm] 'rd, 'fs1");
1219 break;
1220 case 0b00011: // RO_FCVT_LU_S
1221 Format(instr, "fcvt.lu.s ['frm] 'rd, 'fs1");
1222 break;
1223#endif /* V8_TARGET_ARCH_64_BIT */
1224 default:
1225 UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
1226 }
1227 break;
1228 }
1229 case RO_FMV: { // RO_FCLASS_S
1230 if (instr->Rs2Value() != 0b00000) {
1231 UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
1232 }
1233 switch (instr->Funct3Value()) {
1234 case 0b000: // RO_FMV_X_W
1235 Format(instr, "fmv.x.w 'rd, 'fs1");
1236 break;
1237 case 0b001: // RO_FCLASS_S
1238 Format(instr, "fclass.s 'rd, 'fs1");
1239 break;
1240 default:
1241 UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
1242 }
1243 break;
1244 }
1245 case RO_FLE_S: { // RO_FEQ_S RO_FLT_S RO_FLE_S
1246 switch (instr->Funct3Value()) {
1247 case 0b010: // RO_FEQ_S
1248 Format(instr, "feq.s 'rd, 'fs1, 'fs2");
1249 break;
1250 case 0b001: // RO_FLT_S
1251 Format(instr, "flt.s 'rd, 'fs1, 'fs2");
1252 break;
1253 case 0b000: // RO_FLE_S
1254 Format(instr, "fle.s 'rd, 'fs1, 'fs2");
1255 break;
1256 default:
1257 UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
1258 }
1259 break;
1260 }
1261 case RO_FCVT_S_W: { // RO_FCVT_S_WU , 64F RO_FCVT_S_L RO_FCVT_S_LU
1262 switch (instr->Rs2Value()) {
1263 case 0b00000: // RO_FCVT_S_W
1264 Format(instr, "fcvt.s.w 'fd, 'rs1");
1265 break;
1266 case 0b00001: // RO_FCVT_S_WU
1267 Format(instr, "fcvt.s.wu 'fd, 'rs1");
1268 break;
1269#ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_64_BIT
1270 case 0b00010: // RO_FCVT_S_L
1271 Format(instr, "fcvt.s.l 'fd, 'rs1");
1272 break;
1273 case 0b00011: // RO_FCVT_S_LU
1274 Format(instr, "fcvt.s.lu 'fd, 'rs1");
1275 break;
1276#endif /* V8_TARGET_ARCH_64_BIT */
1277 default: {
1278 UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
1279 }
1280 }
1281 break;
1282 }
1283 case RO_FMV_W_X: {
1284 if (instr->Funct3Value() == 0b000) {
1285 Format(instr, "fmv.w.x 'fd, 'rs1");
1286 } else {
1287 UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
1288 }
1289 break;
1290 }
1291 // TODO(riscv): Add macro for RISCV D extension
1292 case RO_FADD_D:
1293 Format(instr, "fadd.d 'fd, 'fs1, 'fs2");
1294 break;
1295 case RO_FSUB_D:
1296 Format(instr, "fsub.d 'fd, 'fs1, 'fs2");
1297 break;
1298 case RO_FMUL_D:
1299 Format(instr, "fmul.d 'fd, 'fs1, 'fs2");
1300 break;
1301 case RO_FDIV_D:
1302 Format(instr, "fdiv.d 'fd, 'fs1, 'fs2");
1303 break;
1304 case RO_FSQRT_D: {
1305 if (instr->Rs2Value() == 0b00000) {
1306 Format(instr, "fsqrt.d 'fd, 'fs1");
1307 } else {
1308 UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
1309 }
1310 break;
1311 }
1312 case RO_FSGNJ_D: { // RO_FSGNJN_D RO_FSGNJX_D
1313 switch (instr->Funct3Value()) {
1314 case 0b000: // RO_FSGNJ_D
1315 if (instr->Rs1Value() == instr->Rs2Value())
1316 Format(instr, "fmv.d 'fd, 'fs1");
1317 else
1318 Format(instr, "fsgnj.d 'fd, 'fs1, 'fs2");
1319 break;
1320 case 0b001: // RO_FSGNJN_D
1321 if (instr->Rs1Value() == instr->Rs2Value())
1322 Format(instr, "fneg.d 'fd, 'fs1");
1323 else
1324 Format(instr, "fsgnjn.d 'fd, 'fs1, 'fs2");
1325 break;
1326 case 0b010: // RO_FSGNJX_D
1327 if (instr->Rs1Value() == instr->Rs2Value())
1328 Format(instr, "fabs.d 'fd, 'fs1");
1329 else
1330 Format(instr, "fsgnjx.d 'fd, 'fs1, 'fs2");
1331 break;
1332 default:
1333 UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
1334 }
1335 break;
1336 }
1337 case RO_FMIN_D: { // RO_FMAX_D
1338 switch (instr->Funct3Value()) {
1339 case 0b000: // RO_FMIN_D
1340 Format(instr, "fmin.d 'fd, 'fs1, 'fs2");
1341 break;
1342 case 0b001: // RO_FMAX_D
1343 Format(instr, "fmax.d 'fd, 'fs1, 'fs2");
1344 break;
1345 default:
1346 UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
1347 }
1348 break;
1349 }
1350 case (RO_FCVT_S_D & kRFPTypeMask): {
1351 if (instr->Rs2Value() == 0b00001) {
1352 Format(instr, "fcvt.s.d ['frm] 'fd, 'fs1");
1353 } else {
1354 UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
1355 }
1356 break;
1357 }
1358 case RO_FCVT_D_S: {
1359 if (instr->Rs2Value() == 0b00000) {
1360 Format(instr, "fcvt.d.s 'fd, 'fs1");
1361 } else {
1362 UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
1363 }
1364 break;
1365 }
1366 case RO_FLE_D: { // RO_FEQ_D RO_FLT_D RO_FLE_D
1367 switch (instr->Funct3Value()) {
1368 case 0b010: // RO_FEQ_S
1369 Format(instr, "feq.d 'rd, 'fs1, 'fs2");
1370 break;
1371 case 0b001: // RO_FLT_D
1372 Format(instr, "flt.d 'rd, 'fs1, 'fs2");
1373 break;
1374 case 0b000: // RO_FLE_D
1375 Format(instr, "fle.d 'rd, 'fs1, 'fs2");
1376 break;
1377 default:
1378 UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
1379 }
1380 break;
1381 }
1382 case (RO_FCLASS_D & kRFPTypeMask): { // RO_FCLASS_D , 64D RO_FMV_X_D
1383 if (instr->Rs2Value() != 0b00000) {
1384 UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
1385 }
1386 switch (instr->Funct3Value()) {
1387 case 0b001: // RO_FCLASS_D
1388 Format(instr, "fclass.d 'rd, 'fs1");
1389 break;
1390#ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_64_BIT
1391 case 0b000: // RO_FMV_X_D
1392 Format(instr, "fmv.x.d 'rd, 'fs1");
1393 break;
1394#endif /* V8_TARGET_ARCH_64_BIT */
1395 default:
1396 UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
1397 }
1398 break;
1399 }
1400 case RO_FCVT_W_D: { // RO_FCVT_WU_D , 64F RO_FCVT_L_D RO_FCVT_LU_D
1401 switch (instr->Rs2Value()) {
1402 case 0b00000: // RO_FCVT_W_D
1403 Format(instr, "fcvt.w.d ['frm] 'rd, 'fs1");
1404 break;
1405 case 0b00001: // RO_FCVT_WU_D
1406 Format(instr, "fcvt.wu.d ['frm] 'rd, 'fs1");
1407 break;
1408#ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_64_BIT
1409 case 0b00010: // RO_FCVT_L_D
1410 Format(instr, "fcvt.l.d ['frm] 'rd, 'fs1");
1411 break;
1412 case 0b00011: // RO_FCVT_LU_D
1413 Format(instr, "fcvt.lu.d ['frm] 'rd, 'fs1");
1414 break;
1415#endif /* V8_TARGET_ARCH_64_BIT */
1416 default:
1417 UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
1418 }
1419 break;
1420 }
1421 case RO_FCVT_D_W: { // RO_FCVT_D_WU , 64F RO_FCVT_D_L RO_FCVT_D_LU
1422 switch (instr->Rs2Value()) {
1423 case 0b00000: // RO_FCVT_D_W
1424 Format(instr, "fcvt.d.w 'fd, 'rs1");
1425 break;
1426 case 0b00001: // RO_FCVT_D_WU
1427 Format(instr, "fcvt.d.wu 'fd, 'rs1");
1428 break;
1429#ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_64_BIT
1430 case 0b00010: // RO_FCVT_D_L
1431 Format(instr, "fcvt.d.l 'fd, 'rs1");
1432 break;
1433 case 0b00011: // RO_FCVT_D_LU
1434 Format(instr, "fcvt.d.lu 'fd, 'rs1");
1435 break;
1436#endif /* V8_TARGET_ARCH_64_BIT */
1437 default:
1438 UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
1439 }
1440 break;
1441 }
1442#ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_64_BIT
1443 case RO_FMV_D_X: {
1444 if (instr->Funct3Value() == 0b000 && instr->Rs2Value() == 0b00000) {
1445 Format(instr, "fmv.d.x 'fd, 'rs1");
1446 } else {
1447 UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
1448 }
1449 break;
1450 }
1451#endif /* V8_TARGET_ARCH_64_BIT */
1452 default: {
1453 UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
1454 }
1455 }
1456}
1457
1458void Decoder::DecodeR4Type(Instruction* instr) {
1459 switch (instr->InstructionBits() & kR4TypeMask) {
1460 // TODO(riscv): use F Extension macro block
1461 case RO_FMADD_S:
1462 Format(instr, "fmadd.s 'fd, 'fs1, 'fs2, 'fs3");
1463 break;
1464 case RO_FMSUB_S:
1465 Format(instr, "fmsub.s 'fd, 'fs1, 'fs2, 'fs3");
1466 break;
1467 case RO_FNMSUB_S:
1468 Format(instr, "fnmsub.s 'fd, 'fs1, 'fs2, 'fs3");
1469 break;
1470 case RO_FNMADD_S:
1471 Format(instr, "fnmadd.s 'fd, 'fs1, 'fs2, 'fs3");
1472 break;
1473 // TODO(riscv): use F Extension macro block
1474 case RO_FMADD_D:
1475 Format(instr, "fmadd.d 'fd, 'fs1, 'fs2, 'fs3");
1476 break;
1477 case RO_FMSUB_D:
1478 Format(instr, "fmsub.d 'fd, 'fs1, 'fs2, 'fs3");
1479 break;
1480 case RO_FNMSUB_D:
1481 Format(instr, "fnmsub.d 'fd, 'fs1, 'fs2, 'fs3");
1482 break;
1483 case RO_FNMADD_D:
1484 Format(instr, "fnmadd.d 'fd, 'fs1, 'fs2, 'fs3");
1485 break;
1486 default:
1487 UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
1488 }
1489}
1490
1491void Decoder::DecodeIType(Instruction* instr) {
1492 switch (instr->InstructionBits() & kITypeMask) {
1493 case RO_JALR:
1494 if (instr->RdValue() == zero_reg.code() &&
1495 instr->Rs1Value() == ra.code() && instr->Imm12Value() == 0)
1496 Format(instr, "ret");
1497 else if (instr->RdValue() == zero_reg.code() && instr->Imm12Value() == 0)
1498 Format(instr, "jr 'rs1");
1499 else if (instr->RdValue() == ra.code() && instr->Imm12Value() == 0)
1500 Format(instr, "jalr 'rs1");
1501 else
1502 Format(instr, "jalr 'rd, 'imm12('rs1)");
1503 break;
1504 case RO_LB:
1505 Format(instr, "lb 'rd, 'imm12('rs1)");
1506 break;
1507 case RO_LH:
1508 Format(instr, "lh 'rd, 'imm12('rs1)");
1509 break;
1510 case RO_LW:
1511 Format(instr, "lw 'rd, 'imm12('rs1)");
1512 break;
1513 case RO_LBU:
1514 Format(instr, "lbu 'rd, 'imm12('rs1)");
1515 break;
1516 case RO_LHU:
1517 Format(instr, "lhu 'rd, 'imm12('rs1)");
1518 break;
1519#ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_64_BIT
1520 case RO_LWU:
1521 Format(instr, "lwu 'rd, 'imm12('rs1)");
1522 break;
1523 case RO_LD:
1524 Format(instr, "ld 'rd, 'imm12('rs1)");
1525 break;
1526#endif /*V8_TARGET_ARCH_64_BIT*/
1527 case RO_ADDI:
1528 if (instr->Imm12Value() == 0) {
1529 if (instr->RdValue() == zero_reg.code() &&
1530 instr->Rs1Value() == zero_reg.code())
1531 Format(instr, "nop");
1532 else
1533 Format(instr, "mv 'rd, 'rs1");
1534 } else if (instr->Rs1Value() == zero_reg.code()) {
1535 Format(instr, "li 'rd, 'imm12");
1536 } else {
1537 Format(instr, "addi 'rd, 'rs1, 'imm12");
1538 }
1539 break;
1540 case RO_SLTI:
1541 Format(instr, "slti 'rd, 'rs1, 'imm12");
1542 break;
1543 case RO_SLTIU:
1544 if (instr->Imm12Value() == 1)
1545 Format(instr, "seqz 'rd, 'rs1");
1546 else
1547 Format(instr, "sltiu 'rd, 'rs1, 'imm12");
1548 break;
1549 case RO_XORI:
1550 if (instr->Imm12Value() == -1)
1551 Format(instr, "not 'rd, 'rs1");
1552 else
1553 Format(instr, "xori 'rd, 'rs1, 'imm12x");
1554 break;
1555 case RO_ORI:
1556 Format(instr, "ori 'rd, 'rs1, 'imm12x");
1557 break;
1558 case RO_ANDI:
1559 Format(instr, "andi 'rd, 'rs1, 'imm12x");
1560 break;
1561 case OP_SHL:
1562 switch (instr->Funct6FieldRaw() | OP_SHL) {
1563 case RO_SLLI:
1564 Format(instr, "slli 'rd, 'rs1, 's64");
1565 break;
1566 case RO_BCLRI:
1567 Format(instr, "bclri 'rd, 'rs1, 's64");
1568 break;
1569 case RO_BINVI:
1570 Format(instr, "binvi 'rd, 'rs1, 's64");
1571 break;
1572 case RO_BSETI:
1573 Format(instr, "bseti 'rd, 'rs1, 's64");
1574 break;
1575 case OP_COUNT:
1576 switch (instr->Shamt()) {
1577 case 0:
1578 Format(instr, "clz 'rd, 'rs1");
1579 break;
1580 case 1:
1581 Format(instr, "ctz 'rd, 'rs1");
1582 break;
1583 case 2:
1584 Format(instr, "cpop 'rd, 'rs1");
1585 break;
1586 case 4:
1587 Format(instr, "sext.b 'rd, 'rs1");
1588 break;
1589 case 5:
1590 Format(instr, "sext.h 'rd, 'rs1");
1591 break;
1592 default:
1593 UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
1594 }
1595 break;
1596 default:
1597 UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
1598 }
1599 break;
1600 case OP_SHR: { // RO_SRAI
1601 switch (instr->Funct6FieldRaw() | OP_SHR) {
1602 case RO_SRLI:
1603 Format(instr, "srli 'rd, 'rs1, 's64");
1604 break;
1605 case RO_SRAI:
1606 Format(instr, "srai 'rd, 'rs1, 's64");
1607 break;
1608 case RO_BEXTI:
1609 Format(instr, "bexti 'rd, 'rs1, 's64");
1610 break;
1611 case RO_ORCB&(kFunct6Mask | OP_SHR):
1612 Format(instr, "orc.b 'rd, 'rs1");
1613 break;
1614 case RO_RORI:
1615#ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_64_BIT
1616 Format(instr, "rori 'rd, 'rs1, 's64");
1617 break;
1618#elif defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32)
1619 Format(instr, "rori 'rd, 'rs1, 's32");
1620 break;
1621#endif
1622 case RO_REV8: {
1623 if (instr->Imm12Value() == RO_REV8_IMM12) {
1624 Format(instr, "rev8 'rd, 'rs1");
1625 break;
1626 }
1627 UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
1628 }
1629 default:
1630 UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
1631 }
1632 break;
1633 }
1634#ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_64_BIT
1635 case RO_ADDIW:
1636 if (instr->Imm12Value() == 0)
1637 Format(instr, "sext.w 'rd, 'rs1");
1638 else
1639 Format(instr, "addiw 'rd, 'rs1, 'imm12");
1640 break;
1641 case OP_SHLW:
1642 switch (instr->Funct7FieldRaw() | OP_SHLW) {
1643 case RO_SLLIW:
1644 Format(instr, "slliw 'rd, 'rs1, 's32");
1645 break;
1646 case RO_SLLIUW:
1647 Format(instr, "slli.uw 'rd, 'rs1, 's32");
1648 break;
1649 case OP_COUNTW: {
1650 switch (instr->Shamt()) {
1651 case 0:
1652 Format(instr, "clzw 'rd, 'rs1");
1653 break;
1654 case 1:
1655 Format(instr, "ctzw 'rd, 'rs1");
1656 break;
1657 case 2:
1658 Format(instr, "cpopw 'rd, 'rs1");
1659 break;
1660 default:
1661 UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
1662 }
1663 break;
1664 }
1665 default:
1666 UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
1667 }
1668 break;
1669 case OP_SHRW: { // RO_SRAI
1670 switch (instr->Funct7FieldRaw() | OP_SHRW) {
1671 case RO_SRLIW:
1672 Format(instr, "srliw 'rd, 'rs1, 's32");
1673 break;
1674 case RO_SRAIW:
1675 Format(instr, "sraiw 'rd, 'rs1, 's32");
1676 break;
1677 case RO_RORIW:
1678 Format(instr, "roriw 'rd, 'rs1, 's32");
1679 break;
1680 default:
1681 UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
1682 }
1683 break;
1684 }
1685#endif /*V8_TARGET_ARCH_64_BIT*/
1686 case RO_FENCE:
1687 if (instr->MemoryOrder(true) == PSIORW &&
1688 instr->MemoryOrder(false) == PSIORW)
1689 Format(instr, "fence");
1690 else
1691 Format(instr, "fence 'pre, 'suc");
1692 break;
1693 case RO_ECALL: { // RO_EBREAK
1694 if (instr->Imm12Value() == 0) { // ECALL
1695 Format(instr, "ecall");
1696 } else if (instr->Imm12Value() == 1) { // EBREAK
1697 Format(instr, "ebreak");
1698 } else {
1699 UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
1700 }
1701 break;
1702 }
1703 // TODO(riscv): use Zifencei Standard Extension macro block
1704 case RO_FENCE_I:
1705 Format(instr, "fence.i");
1706 break;
1707 // TODO(riscv): use Zicsr Standard Extension macro block
1708 // FIXME(RISC-V): Add special formatting for CSR registers
1709 case RO_CSRRW:
1710 if (instr->CsrValue() == csr_fcsr) {
1711 if (instr->RdValue() == zero_reg.code())
1712 Format(instr, "fscsr 'rs1");
1713 else
1714 Format(instr, "fscsr 'rd, 'rs1");
1715 } else if (instr->CsrValue() == csr_frm) {
1716 if (instr->RdValue() == zero_reg.code())
1717 Format(instr, "fsrm 'rs1");
1718 else
1719 Format(instr, "fsrm 'rd, 'rs1");
1720 } else if (instr->CsrValue() == csr_fflags) {
1721 if (instr->RdValue() == zero_reg.code())
1722 Format(instr, "fsflags 'rs1");
1723 else
1724 Format(instr, "fsflags 'rd, 'rs1");
1725 } else if (instr->RdValue() == zero_reg.code()) {
1726 Format(instr, "csrw 'csr, 'rs1");
1727 } else {
1728 Format(instr, "csrrw 'rd, 'csr, 'rs1");
1729 }
1730 break;
1731 case RO_CSRRS:
1732 if (instr->Rs1Value() == zero_reg.code()) {
1733 switch (instr->CsrValue()) {
1734 case csr_instret:
1735 Format(instr, "rdinstret 'rd");
1736 break;
1737 case csr_instreth:
1738 Format(instr, "rdinstreth 'rd");
1739 break;
1740 case csr_time:
1741 Format(instr, "rdtime 'rd");
1742 break;
1743 case csr_timeh:
1744 Format(instr, "rdtimeh 'rd");
1745 break;
1746 case csr_cycle:
1747 Format(instr, "rdcycle 'rd");
1748 break;
1749 case csr_cycleh:
1750 Format(instr, "rdcycleh 'rd");
1751 break;
1752 case csr_fflags:
1753 Format(instr, "frflags 'rd");
1754 break;
1755 case csr_frm:
1756 Format(instr, "frrm 'rd");
1757 break;
1758 case csr_fcsr:
1759 Format(instr, "frcsr 'rd");
1760 break;
1761 default:
1762 UNREACHABLE();
1763 }
1764 } else if (instr->Rs1Value() == zero_reg.code()) {
1765 Format(instr, "csrr 'rd, 'csr");
1766 } else if (instr->RdValue() == zero_reg.code()) {
1767 Format(instr, "csrs 'csr, 'rs1");
1768 } else {
1769 Format(instr, "csrrs 'rd, 'csr, 'rs1");
1770 }
1771 break;
1772 case RO_CSRRC:
1773 if (instr->RdValue() == zero_reg.code())
1774 Format(instr, "csrc 'csr, 'rs1");
1775 else
1776 Format(instr, "csrrc 'rd, 'csr, 'rs1");
1777 break;
1778 case RO_CSRRWI:
1779 if (instr->RdValue() == zero_reg.code())
1780 Format(instr, "csrwi 'csr, 'uimm");
1781 else
1782 Format(instr, "csrrwi 'rd, 'csr, 'uimm");
1783 break;
1784 case RO_CSRRSI:
1785 if (instr->RdValue() == zero_reg.code())
1786 Format(instr, "csrsi 'csr, 'uimm");
1787 else
1788 Format(instr, "csrrsi 'rd, 'csr, 'uimm");
1789 break;
1790 case RO_CSRRCI:
1791 if (instr->RdValue() == zero_reg.code())
1792 Format(instr, "csrci 'csr, 'uimm");
1793 else
1794 Format(instr, "csrrci 'rd, 'csr, 'uimm");
1795 break;
1796 // TODO(riscv): use F Extension macro block
1797 case RO_FLW:
1798 Format(instr, "flw 'fd, 'imm12('rs1)");
1799 break;
1800 // TODO(riscv): use D Extension macro block
1801 case RO_FLD:
1802 Format(instr, "fld 'fd, 'imm12('rs1)");
1803 break;
1804 default:
1805#ifdef CAN_USE_RVV_INSTRUCTIONS
1806 if (instr->vl_vs_width() != -1) {
1807 DecodeRvvVL(instr);
1808 } else {
1809 UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
1810 }
1811 break;
1812#else
1813 UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
1814#endif
1815 }
1816}

1818void Decoder::DecodeSType(Instruction* instr) {
1819 switch (instr->InstructionBits() & kSTypeMask) {
1820 case RO_SB:
1821 Format(instr, "sb 'rs2, 'offS('rs1)");
1822 break;
1823 case RO_SH:
1824 Format(instr, "sh 'rs2, 'offS('rs1)");
1825 break;
1826 case RO_SW:
1827 Format(instr, "sw 'rs2, 'offS('rs1)");
1828 break;
1829#ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_64_BIT
1830 case RO_SD:
1831 Format(instr, "sd 'rs2, 'offS('rs1)");
1832 break;
1833#endif /*V8_TARGET_ARCH_64_BIT*/
1834 // TODO(riscv): use F Extension macro block
1835 case RO_FSW:
1836 Format(instr, "fsw 'fs2, 'offS('rs1)");
1837 break;
1838 // TODO(riscv): use D Extension macro block
1839 case RO_FSD:
1840 Format(instr, "fsd 'fs2, 'offS('rs1)");
1841 break;
1842 default:
1843#ifdef CAN_USE_RVV_INSTRUCTIONS
1844 if (instr->vl_vs_width() != -1) {
1845 DecodeRvvVS(instr);
1846 } else {
1847 UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
1848 }
1849 break;
1850#else
1851 UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
1852#endif
1853 }
1854}

1880void Decoder::DecodeUType(Instruction* instr) {
1881 // U Type doesn't have additional mask
1882 switch (instr->BaseOpcodeFieldRaw()) {
1883 case LUI:
1884 Format(instr, "lui 'rd, 'imm20U");
1885 break;
1886 case AUIPC:
1887 Format(instr, "auipc 'rd, 'imm20U");
1888 break;
1889 default:
1890 UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
1891 }
1892}
1893// namespace internal
1894void Decoder::DecodeJType(Instruction* instr) {
1895 // J Type doesn't have additional mask
1896 switch (instr->BaseOpcodeValue()) {
1897 case JAL:
1898 if (instr->RdValue() == zero_reg.code())
1899 Format(instr, "j 'imm20J");
1900 else if (instr->RdValue() == ra.code())
1901 Format(instr, "jal 'imm20J");
1902 else
1903 Format(instr, "jal 'rd, 'imm20J");
1904 break;
1905 default:
1906 UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
1907 }
1908}
1909
1910void Decoder::DecodeCRType(Instruction* instr) {
1911 switch (instr->RvcFunct4Value()) {
1912 case 0b1000:
1913 if (instr->RvcRs1Value() != 0 && instr->RvcRs2Value() == 0) {
1914 Format(instr, "jr 'Crs1");
1915 break;
1916 } else if (instr->RvcRdValue() != 0 && instr->RvcRs2Value() != 0) {
1917 Format(instr, "mv 'Crd, 'Crs2");
1918 break;
1919 } else {
1920 UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
1921 }
1922 case 0b1001:
1923 if (instr->RvcRs1Value() == 0 && instr->RvcRs2Value() == 0) {
1924 Format(instr, "ebreak");
1925 break;
1926 } else if (instr->RvcRdValue() != 0 && instr->RvcRs2Value() == 0) {
1927 Format(instr, "jalr 'Crs1");
1928 break;
1929 } else if (instr->RvcRdValue() != 0 && instr->RvcRs2Value() != 0) {
1930 Format(instr, "add 'Crd, 'Crd, 'Crs2");
1931 break;
1932 } else {
1933 UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
1934 }
1935 default:
1936 UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
1937 }
1938}

1967void Decoder::DecodeCIType(Instruction* instr) {
1968 switch (instr->RvcOpcode()) {
1969 case RO_C_NOP_ADDI:
1970 if (instr->RvcRdValue() == 0)
1971 Format(instr, "nop");
1972 else
1973 Format(instr, "addi 'Crd, 'Crd, 'Cimm6");
1974 break;
1975#ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_64_BIT
1976 case RO_C_ADDIW:
1977 Format(instr, "addiw 'Crd, 'Crd, 'Cimm6");
1978 break;
1979#endif
1980 case RO_C_LI:
1981 Format(instr, "li 'Crd, 'Cimm6");
1982 break;
1983 case RO_C_LUI_ADD:
1984 if (instr->RvcRdValue() == 2) {
1985 Format(instr, "addi sp, sp, 'Cimm6Addi16sp");
1986 break;
1987 } else if (instr->RvcRdValue() != 0 && instr->RvcRdValue() != 2) {
1988 Format(instr, "lui 'Crd, 'Cimm6U");
1989 break;
1990 } else {
1991 UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
1992 }
1993 case RO_C_SLLI:
1994 Format(instr, "slli 'Crd, 'Crd, 'Cshamt");
1995 break;
1996 case RO_C_FLDSP:
1997 Format(instr, "fld 'Cfd, 'Cimm6Ldsp(sp)");
1998 break;
1999 case RO_C_LWSP:
2000 Format(instr, "lw 'Crd, 'Cimm6Lwsp(sp)");
2001 break;
2002#ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_64_BIT
2003 case RO_C_LDSP:
2004 Format(instr, "ld 'Crd, 'Cimm6Ldsp(sp)");
2005 break;
2006#elif defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_32_BIT)
2007 case RO_C_FLWSP:
2008 Format(instr, "flw 'Cfd, 'Cimm6Ldsp(sp)");
2009 break;
2010#endif
2011 default:
2012 UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
2013 }

2450void Decoder::DecodeRvvMVV(Instruction* instr) {
2451 DCHECK_EQ(instr->InstructionBits() & (kBaseOpcodeMask | kFunct3Mask), OP_MVV);
2452 switch (instr->InstructionBits() & kVTypeMask) {
2453 case RO_V_VMUNARY0: {
2454 if (instr->Vs1Value() == VID_V) {
2455 Format(instr, "vid.v 'rd, 'vs2'vm");
2456 } else {
2457 UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
2458 }
2459 break;
2460 }
2461 case RO_V_VWXUNARY0:
2462 if (instr->Vs1Value() == 0x0) {
2463 Format(instr, "vmv.x.s 'rd, 'vs2");
2464 } else if (instr->Vs1Value() == 0b10001) {
2465 Format(instr, "vfirst.m 'rd, 'vs2");
2466 } else if (instr->Vs1Value() == 0b10000) {
2467 Format(instr, "vcpop.m 'rd, 'vs2");
2468 } else {
2469 UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
2470 }
2471 break;
2472 case RO_V_VREDMAXU:
2473 Format(instr, "vredmaxu.vs 'vd, 'vs2, 'vs1'vm");
2474 break;
2475 case RO_V_VREDMAX:
2476 Format(instr, "vredmax.vs 'vd, 'vs2, 'vs1'vm");
2477 break;
2478 case RO_V_VREDMIN:
2479 Format(instr, "vredmin.vs 'vd, 'vs2, 'vs1'vm");
2480 break;
2481 case RO_V_VREDMINU:
2482 Format(instr, "vredminu.vs 'vd, 'vs2, 'vs1'vm");
2483 break;
2484 case RO_V_VXUNARY0:
2485 if (instr->Vs1Value() == 0b00010) {
2486 Format(instr, "vzext.vf8 'vd, 'vs2'vm");
2487 } else if (instr->Vs1Value() == 0b00011) {
2488 Format(instr, "vsext.vf8 'vd, 'vs2'vm");
2489 } else if (instr->Vs1Value() == 0b00100) {

2854void Decoder::DecodeVType(Instruction* instr) {
2855 switch (instr->InstructionBits() & (kBaseOpcodeMask | kFunct3Mask)) {
2856 case OP_IVV:
2857 DecodeRvvIVV(instr);
2858 return;
2859 case OP_FVV:
2860 DecodeRvvFVV(instr);
2861 return;
2862 case OP_MVV:
2863 DecodeRvvMVV(instr);
2864 return;
2865 case OP_IVI:
2866 DecodeRvvIVI(instr);
2867 return;
2868 case OP_IVX:
2869 DecodeRvvIVX(instr);
2870 return;
2871 case OP_FVF:
2872 DecodeRvvFVF(instr);
2873 return;
2874 case OP_MVX:
2875 DecodeRvvMVX(instr);
2876 return;
2877 }
2878 switch (instr->InstructionBits() &
2879 (kBaseOpcodeMask | kFunct3Mask | 0x80000000)) {
2880 case RO_V_VSETVLI:
2881 Format(instr, "vsetvli 'rd, 'rs1, 'sew, 'lmul");
2882 break;
2883 case RO_V_VSETVL:
2884 if (!(instr->InstructionBits() & 0x40000000)) {
2885 Format(instr, "vsetvl 'rd, 'rs1, 'rs2");
2886 } else {
2887 Format(instr, "vsetivli 'rd, 'uimm, 'sew, 'lmul");
2888 }
2889 break;
2890 default:
2891 UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
2892 }
2893}
2894int Decoder::switch_nf(Instruction* instr) {
2895 int nf = 0;
2896 switch (instr->InstructionBits() & kRvvNfMask) {
2897 case 0x20000000:
2898 nf = 2;
2899 break;
2900 case 0x40000000:
2901 nf = 3;
2902 break;
2903 case 0x60000000:
2904 nf = 4;
2905 break;
2906 case 0x80000000:
2907 nf = 5;
2908 break;
2909 case 0xa0000000:
2910 nf = 6;
2911 break;
2912 case 0xc0000000:
2913 nf = 7;
2914 break;
2915 case 0xe0000000:
2916 nf = 8;
2917 break;
2918 }
2919 return nf;
2920}
2921void Decoder::DecodeRvvVL(Instruction* instr) {
2922 char str[50];
2923 uint32_t instr_temp =
2924 instr->InstructionBits() & (kRvvMopMask | kRvvNfMask | kBaseOpcodeMask);
2925 // switch (instr->InstructionBits() &
2926 // (kRvvMopMask | kRvvNfMask | kBaseOpcodeMask)) {
2927 if (RO_V_VL == instr_temp) {
2928 if (!(instr->InstructionBits() & (kRvvRs2Mask))) {
2929 snprintf(str, sizeof(str), "vle%d.v 'vd, ('rs1)'vm",
2930 instr->vl_vs_width());
2931 Format(instr, str);
2932 } else {
2933 snprintf(str, sizeof(str), "vle%dff.v 'vd, ('rs1)'vm",
2934 instr->vl_vs_width());
2935 Format(instr, str);
2936 }
2937 } else if (RO_V_VLS == instr_temp) {
2938 snprintf(str, sizeof(str), "vlse%d.v 'vd, ('rs1), 'rs2'vm",
2939 instr->vl_vs_width());
2940 Format(instr, str);
2941
2942 } else if (RO_V_VLX == instr_temp) {
2943 snprintf(str, sizeof(str), "vlxei%d.v 'vd, ('rs1), 'vs2'vm",
2944 instr->vl_vs_width());
2945 Format(instr, str);
2946 } else if (RO_V_VLSEG2 == instr_temp || RO_V_VLSEG3 == instr_temp ||
2947 RO_V_VLSEG4 == instr_temp || RO_V_VLSEG5 == instr_temp ||
2948 RO_V_VLSEG6 == instr_temp || RO_V_VLSEG7 == instr_temp ||
2949 RO_V_VLSEG8 == instr_temp) {
2950 if (!(instr->InstructionBits() & (kRvvRs2Mask))) {
2951 snprintf(str, sizeof(str), "vlseg%de%d.v 'vd, ('rs1)'vm",
2952 switch_nf(instr), instr->vl_vs_width());
2953 } else {
2954 snprintf(str, sizeof(str), "vlseg%de%dff.v 'vd, ('rs1)'vm",
2955 switch_nf(instr), instr->vl_vs_width());
2956 }
2957 Format(instr, str);
2958 } else if (RO_V_VLSSEG2 == instr_temp || RO_V_VLSSEG3 == instr_temp ||
2959 RO_V_VLSSEG4 == instr_temp || RO_V_VLSSEG5 == instr_temp ||
2960 RO_V_VLSSEG6 == instr_temp || RO_V_VLSSEG7 == instr_temp ||
2961 RO_V_VLSSEG8 == instr_temp) {
2962 snprintf(str, sizeof(str), "vlsseg%de%d.v 'vd, ('rs1), 'rs2'vm",
2963 switch_nf(instr), instr->vl_vs_width());
2964 Format(instr, str);
2965 } else if (RO_V_VLXSEG2 == instr_temp || RO_V_VLXSEG3 == instr_temp ||
2966 RO_V_VLXSEG4 == instr_temp || RO_V_VLXSEG5 == instr_temp ||
2967 RO_V_VLXSEG6 == instr_temp || RO_V_VLXSEG7 == instr_temp ||
2968 RO_V_VLXSEG8 == instr_temp) {
2969 snprintf(str, sizeof(str), "vlxseg%dei%d.v 'vd, ('rs1), 'vs2'vm",
2970 switch_nf(instr), instr->vl_vs_width());
2971 Format(instr, str);
2972 }
2973}
2974
2975int Decoder::switch_sew(Instruction* instr) {
2976 int width = 0;
2977 if ((instr->InstructionBits() & kBaseOpcodeMask) != LOAD_FP &&
2978 (instr->InstructionBits() & kBaseOpcodeMask) != STORE_FP)
2979 return -1;
2980 switch (instr->InstructionBits() & (kRvvWidthMask | kRvvMewMask)) {
2981 case 0x0:
2982 width = 8;
2983 break;
2984 case 0x00005000:
2985 width = 16;
2986 break;
2987 case 0x00006000:
2988 width = 32;
2989 break;
2990 case 0x00007000:
2991 width = 64;
2992 break;
2993 case 0x10000000:
2994 width = 128;
2995 break;
2996 case 0x10005000:
2997 width = 256;
2998 break;
2999 case 0x10006000:
3000 width = 512;
3001 break;
3002 case 0x10007000:
3003 width = 1024;
3004 break;
3005 default:
3006 width = -1;
3007 break;
3008 }
3009 return width;
3010}

3016 if (RO_V_VS == instr_temp) {
3017 snprintf(str, sizeof(str), "vse%d.v 'vd, ('rs1)'vm",

3019 Format(instr, str);
3020 } else if (RO_V_VSS == instr_temp) {

3027 Format(instr, str);

3030 instr->vl_vs_width());
3031 Format(instr, str);
3032 } else if (RO_V_VSSEG2 == instr_temp || RO_V_VSSEG3 == instr_temp ||
3033 RO_V_VSSEG4 == instr_temp || RO_V_VSSEG5 == instr_temp ||
3034 RO_V_VSSEG6 == instr_temp || RO_V_VSSEG7 == instr_temp ||
3035 RO_V_VSSEG8 == instr_temp) {
3036 snprintf(str, sizeof(str), "vsseg%de%d.v 'vd, ('rs1)'vm",
3037 switch_nf(instr), instr->vl_vs_width());
3038 Format(instr, str);
3039 } else if (RO_V_VSSSEG2 == instr_temp || RO_V_VSSSEG3 == instr_temp ||
3040 RO_V_VSSSEG4 == instr_temp || RO_V_VSSSEG5 == instr_temp ||
3041 RO_V_VSSSEG6 == instr_temp || RO_V_VSSSEG7 == instr_temp ||
3042 RO_V_VSSSEG8 == instr_temp) {
3043 snprintf(str, sizeof(str), "vssseg%de%d.v 'vd, ('rs1), 'rs2'vm",
3044 switch_nf(instr), instr->vl_vs_width());
3045 Format(instr, str);
3046 } else if (RO_V_VSXSEG2 == instr_temp || RO_V_VSXSEG3 == instr_temp ||
3047 RO_V_VSXSEG4 == instr_temp || RO_V_VSXSEG5 == instr_temp ||
3048 RO_V_VSXSEG6 == instr_temp || RO_V_VSXSEG7 == instr_temp ||
3049 RO_V_VSXSEG8 == instr_temp) {
3050 snprintf(str, sizeof(str), "vsxseg%dei%d.v 'vd, ('rs1), 'vs2'vm",
3051 switch_nf(instr), instr->vl_vs_width());
3052 Format(instr, str);
3053 }
3054}
3055
3056// Disassemble the instruction at *instr_ptr into the output buffer.
3057// All instructions are one word long, except for the simulator
3058// pseudo-instruction stop(msg). For that one special case, we return
3059// size larger than one kInstrSize.
3060int Decoder::InstructionDecode(uint8_t* instr_ptr) {
3061 Instruction* instr = Instruction::At(instr_ptr);
3062 // Print raw instruction bytes.
3063 out_buffer_pos_ += base::SNPrintF(out_buffer_ + out_buffer_pos_,
3064 "%08x ", instr->InstructionBits());
3065 switch (instr->InstructionType()) {
3066 case Instruction::kRType:
3067 DecodeRType(instr);
3068 break;
3069 case Instruction::kR4Type:
3070 DecodeR4Type(instr);
3071 break;
3072 case Instruction::kIType:
3073 DecodeIType(instr);
3074 break;
3075 case Instruction::kSType:
3076 DecodeSType(instr);
3077 break;
3078 case Instruction::kBType:
3079 DecodeBType(instr);
3080 break;
3081 case Instruction::kUType:
3082 DecodeUType(instr);
3083 break;
3084 case Instruction::kJType:
3085 DecodeJType(instr);
3086 break;
3087 case Instruction::kCRType:
3088 DecodeCRType(instr);
3089 break;
3090 case Instruction::kCAType:
3091 DecodeCAType(instr);
3092 break;
3093 case Instruction::kCJType:
3094 DecodeCJType(instr);
3095 break;
3096 case Instruction::kCIType:
3097 DecodeCIType(instr);
3098 break;
3099 case Instruction::kCIWType:
3100 DecodeCIWType(instr);
3101 break;
3102 case Instruction::kCSSType:
3103 DecodeCSSType(instr);
3104 break;
3105 case Instruction::kCLType:
3106 DecodeCLType(instr);
3107 break;
3108 case Instruction::kCSType:
3109 DecodeCSType(instr);
3110 break;
3111 case Instruction::kCBType:
3112 DecodeCBType(instr);
3113 break;
3114#ifdef CAN_USE_RVV_INSTRUCTIONS
3115 case Instruction::kVType:
3116 DecodeVType(instr);
3117 break;
3118#endif
3119 default:
3120 Format(instr, "UNSUPPORTED");
3121 break;
3122 }
3123 return instr->InstructionSize();
3124}

3171 reinterpret_cast<v8::internal::Instruction*>(instruction));
3172}
3173
3174void Disassembler::Disassemble(FILE* f, uint8_t* begin, uint8_t* end,
3175 UnimplementedOpcodeAction unimplemented_action) {
3176 NameConverter converter;
3177 Disassembler d(converter, unimplemented_action);
3178 for (uint8_t* pc = begin; pc < end;) {
3179 v8::base::EmbeddedVector<char, 128> buffer;
3180 buffer[0] = '\0';
3181 uint8_t* prev_pc = pc;
3182 pc += d.InstructionDecode(buffer, pc);
3183 v8::internal::PrintF(f, "%p %08x %s\n", static_cast<void*>(prev_pc),
3184 *reinterpret_cast<uint32_t*>(prev_pc), buffer.begin());
3185 }
3186}
